do you agree? Proposed Fix Approach

Fix for Root Cause 1 — Shuffle before take

Add a shuffle of both tiers independently before take(max_sources). The rand crate's SliceRandom::shuffle is already a transitive dependency in the workspace (confirm with cargo tree -i rand). If not available, use a Fisher-Yates shuffle seeded from std::time::SystemTime.

// In select_source_candidates, after building tier1 and tier2:
use rand::seq::SliceRandom;
let mut rng = rand::thread_rng();
tier1.shuffle(&mut rng);
tier2.sort_by(|a, b| b.created_at.cmp(&a.created_at)); // keep as tiebreak base
tier2.shuffle(&mut rng);  // OR: shuffle after sort to randomize within equal timestamps
The shuffle must be within each tier independently, not across them, so that tier 1 (isolated) entries still take priority over tier 2 (non-isolated) entries — just not always the same isolated entries.

Fix for Root Cause 2 — Exclude no-embedding entries at Phase 3

Add a new method to VectorIndex: fn embedded_ids(&self) -> HashSet<u64> that reads id_map.entry_to_data.keys() into a HashSet<u64> under a single read lock. This is O(N) once at call site, O(1) per candidate at selection time.

Call it once in run_graph_inference_tick before Phase 3, and pass the result into select_source_candidates:

// In run_graph_inference_tick, before Phase 3:
let embedded_ids: HashSet<u64> = vector_index.embedded_ids();

// In select_source_candidates signature:
fn select_source_candidates(
    all_active: &[EntryRecord],
    _existing_edge_set: &HashSet<(u64, u64)>,
    isolated_ids: &HashSet<u64>,
    embedded_ids: &HashSet<u64>,   // NEW parameter
    max_sources: usize,
) -> Vec<u64>

// In partition loop:
for entry in all_active {
    if !embedded_ids.contains(&entry.id) {
        continue; // skip: no embedding, would be wasted slot
    }
    if isolated_ids.contains(&entry.id) {
        tier1.push(entry);
    } else {
        tier2.push(entry);
    }
}
The existing contains(entry_id: u64) -> bool on VectorIndex is O(1) per call but would require N individual lock acquisitions. The bulk embedded_ids() method acquires the read lock once and produces the full set — preferred for this use case (called once per tick, on potentially thousands of entries).

Required addition to unimatrix_core::VectorStore trait (for object-safety): add fn embedded_ids(&self) -> HashSet<u64>; to the trait definition, then implement on VectorAdapter in adapters.rs.

Why This Fix

Minimal: both changes are confined to select_source_candidates plus one pre-selection line and one new trait/impl method. No schema changes, no new state, no design change.
Correct: the shuffle ensures different candidates are sampled each tick, giving probabilistically complete coverage over all isolated entries. The embedding filter removes permanently-stuck no-embedding entries from both tiers before any slot is allocated to them.
Safe for the existing guarantee: tier 1 still precedes tier 2 after shuffle because both tiers are shuffled independently and then chained in order (tier1 first).
